BEGIN_PGML

Gerri leaves the long jump takeoff board with a vertical velocity of [`[$vx]`] [`m/s`] and a horizontal velocity of [`[$vy]`] [`m/s`].

*a)* What is Gerri's resultant velocity at takeoff?

[`r=`] [_____]{"$r"} [`m/s`]  

*b)* What is Gerri's takeoff angle - the angle of her resultant takeoff velocity with horizontal?

[`\theta=`] [_____]{"$theta"} [`^{\circ}`]  

*c)* What is Gerri's horizontal velocity just before she lands?

[`v_x=`] [_____]{"$vx2"} [`m/s`]  

*d)* If Gerri is in the air for [`[$t]`] [`s`], what is her horizontal displacement during this time in the air?

[`\Delta x=`] [_____]{"$dx"} [`m`]  

*e)* What is Gerri's vertical velocity at the end of her [`[$t]`] [`s`] flight?

[`v_y=`] [_____]{"$vy2"} [`m/s`]  

*f)* If Gerri's center of gravity was [`[$cog]`] [`m`] high at the instant of takeoff, how high will it be at the peak of her flight?

[`y_{peak}=`] [_____]{"$h"} [`m`]  

*g)* How high is Gerri's center of gravity at the end of her flight, when she first hits the pit?

[`y_f=`] [_____]{"$h2"} [`m`]  

END_PGML

